condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Computerized Project Accounting Package - Dated Covenant | Description :The Recipient shall install or caused tobe installed a computerized accounting and financial management system for the Project, acceptable to the Association. | Due Date:16-Dec-2014

Finance Agreement :Counterpart Funding - Recurrent Covenant | Description :The Recipient shall ensure that the total amount of USD5 million equivalent be allocated to the Project on an annual basis through budgetary allocation for the whole period ofimplementation of the Project. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :External Auditors - Dated Covenant | Description :The Recipient shall appoint an external auditor for theProject with qualifications, experience and terms of reference acceptable to the Association. | Due Date :16-Oct-2014

Finance Agreement :Fiduciary Unit of the Project Management Team - Dated Covenant | Description :The Recipient shall appoint to thePMT and maintain, at all times until the completion of the Project, two procurement officers andtwo accountants, all withqualifications, experience and terms of reference acceptable to the Association. | Due Date :16-Sep-2014

Finance Agreement :M&E support - Dated Covenant | Description :The Recipient shall appoint to the PMT and maintain, at all timesuntil the completion of the Project, a senior monitoring and evaluation specialist, with qualifications, experience and terms ofreference acceptable to the Association. | Due Date :16-Sep-2014

Finance Agreement :Update of Cadastro (primary school database) - Recurrent Covenant | Description :The Recipient shall, not laterthan April 30 of each year, starting from April 30, 2014 until the completion of the Project, updatethe Cadastro database through asimple primary school census. | Frequency :Yearly
